               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-244-person1360">
                  FRANCIS 
                  KEYS
               <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1360" type="surname" value="KEYS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1360" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1360" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was on duty in <placeName id="t18280410-244-crimeloc1300">Whitechapel</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-244-crimeloc1300" type="placeName" value="Whitechapel"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-244-crimeloc1300" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-244-off1298 t18280410-244-crimeloc1300"></join> on the 13th of March, and saw the prisoner take this box out of a truck, and run away with it; I pursued, and took him. The box was tied, and locked; I opened it, and found a cap, five lumps of butter, and five towels in it. I have seen the prosecutor, who claimed the property, but he said he was going to sea, and could not come here.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-244-person1361">
                  JOHN 
                  DOWNEY
               <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1361" type="surname" value="DOWNEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1361" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1361" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter. I had an order from Mr. Ogilby, a ship agent, to go and get this box from Horsleydown, for Mr. Henry Johnston; I was going along Whitechapel with it in a truck - I missed the box, and called out to the people to know if they had seen it; the officer came up, and told me to go to the watch-house, where I saw it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-244-person1362">
                  JAMES 
                  STACE
               <interp inst="t18280410-244-person1362" type="surname" value="STACE"></interp>
